\title{cladesR: Identify and Investigate Clades That Depart from Birth-Death Expectations}
\description{
Tools for comparing the sizes of same-aged clades to the geometric distribution expected under a homogeneous birth-death (speciation-extinction) process, flagging clades that contain more or fewer species than expected, and investigating how anomalous clades differ. The geometric progeny-size model and the conditional broken-stick null follow Nee, Mooers & Harvey (1992) \doi{10.1073/pnas.89.17.8322}; the clade-size diagnostics and the diversification-pulse framing follow Ricklefs (2003, 2005, 2014).
